About
The Tower is a unique, iconic fixture in the Vegas skyline with a magnificent 360 degree view of the shimmering Las Vegas Strip and Valley.

    Must see in Vegas
    Went up to the viewing platform on a lovely sunny day for the brilliant views. Did not attempt any of the rides. Nice fast lifts. There are indoor and outdoor areas. A nice bar indoors where you can sit and watch the daredevils leaping off the tower. Well worth a visit
    Visited September 2023
    Traveled with friends
    Written October 3, 2023
  • goodguyjas
    London, United Kingdom1,219 contributions
    Absolutely amazing views day and of course night. An absolute must do!
    Jaw dropping views of the whole of Vegas. Looks amazing day and of course night. The view of the strip with many landmarks easily visible is a sight to behold. Overwhelming. Hundreds of pictures and videos to record. Above is scary rides involving being dropped in a lift or a short rollercoaster that appears to go off the edge and stops just in time. Too much for me. Couldnt contemplate the extreme drops off the top that you can do from here too. Note it can be cold at night so bring something to keep you warm. Great lower level inside with bar, cafe and shop with comfortable seats and the same views behind glass. Elevators work well and there are a few to get you up and down plus stairs for the last few levels. Easy to get to once in Strat Hotel. After a security check then it is up to the top. A must do in Vegas!
    Visited November 2023
    Traveled solo
    Written November 19, 2023
  • Shelley M
    Oklahoma476 contributions
    Cool 360 degree view of Vegas and the area
    Really neat view of Vegas from one of the tallest buildings west of the Mississippi. There are plenty of windows to look through, and touchscreens around the room identify landmarks you see. You can go outside and walk most of the way around and use the pay-binoculars on posts if you want (take quarters). Take all the time you want. If you decide to arrive by monorail, you will have to walk for 10 minutes or so in a rougher part of town.
    Visited November 2023
